content:
Set Up a Call Center

Before Salesforce users can access and use a call center, an administrator must complete various tasks.

Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage call centers, call center users, call center directories, and SoftPhone layouts: Manage Call Centers

Work with a developer or partner to create a computer-telephony integration (CTI) implementation that uses the Open CTI API and works with your existing telephony system.

Assign Salesforce users to the appropriate call center. A call center user must be associated with a call center to view the softphone.
Optionally, you can make further customizations.

Configure call center phone directories with more directory numbers and updated phone number search layouts.
Customize softphone layouts for different user profiles.

Call Center Definition Files
A call center definition file specifies a set of fields and values that are used to define a call center in Salesforce for a particular CTI system.

Create a Call Center Definition File by writing an XML file according to the guidelines outlined in these topics.
Import a Call Center Definition File to create your first call center for a CTI adapter that was just installed.
title: Setting Up a Call Center in Salesforce
